<TITLE> UN's Ban deplores Iranian's comment on Israel </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 UNITED NATIONS, Feb 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon believes comments such as one this week by Iran's president likening Israel to a "savage animal" are inflammatory and unacceptable, his spokeswoman said on Thursday. Iran does not recognize Israel and its hardline President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad has often predicted the imminent demise of the Jewish state. He made his latest comment on Wednesday. "The secretary-general has condemned these types of inflammatory comments in the past and he will continue to do so in the future," UN spokeswoman Michele Montas told a regular news briefing. "He wishes to reiterate that such comments are unacceptable when used against another member state. The secretary-general believes it is in the interest of all member states to pay due respect to each other even when addressing their differences." Israel Radio earlier quoted Ban as telling it he found it "unacceptable and undesirable for a member state ... to use such kind of language against any other member state." Israel's UN ambassador Dan Gillerman told reporters he had raised the issue of Ahmadinejad's comment during a meeting with Ban on Wednesday. Gillerman said that when he detailed the Iranian leader's comment to Ban, "he was visibly shocked by i
